!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

miniature /ˈmɪnɪtʃə/

(miniatures) 

1. ADJ Miniature is used to describe something that is very small, especially a smaller version of something which is normally much bigger. 微型的 [ADJ n] 

例： Rosehill Farm has been selling miniature roses since 

1979. 自1979年起，玫瑰山农场就一直出售袖珍玫瑰。 

2. PHRASE If you describe one thing as another thing in miniature , you mean that it is much smaller in size or scale than the other thing, but is otherwise exactly the same. 缩影 

例： Ecuador provides a perfect introduction to South America; it's a continent in miniature. 厄瓜多尔是南美的一个绝佳概览；它是整个大陆的缩影。 

3. N-COUNT A miniature is a very small, detailed painting, often of a person. 袖珍画像

